{
  "text": "Metabolic syndrome (MetS) is also known to be a risk factor for CVD, T2DM, and all-cause mortality [CITATION_1] . MetS is characterized as a cluster of risk factors including central obesity, hypertension, hyperglycemia, dyslipidemia such as elevated triglyceride (TG), apolipoprotein B (apoB)-containing lipoproteins and low levels of HDL-cholesterol (C) [5] . To reduce the risk of CVD, the normalization of serum levels of lipid such as total cholesterol (TC) or LDL-C is very important to the patients with MetS and T2DM.",
